pull_request.title: feat(category): Implement CRUD pages for admin category management
pull_request.body:
This commit introduces the complete set of CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) pages for managing categories within the admin panel.

- **Presentation Layer:**
  - Added `Create.cshtml` page and its associated PageModel to handle the creation of new categories, including form binding and validation.
  - Added `Edit.cshtml` page and its PageModel for fetching and updating existing category details.
  - Updated the `Index.cshtml` page to display a paginated list of all categories, with links to the Edit page and functionality for deletion.
  - Added a delete confirmation modal to prevent accidental removal of categories.

- **Core Layer:**
  - Created necessary ViewModels (`CreateCategoryViewModel`, `EditCategoryViewModel`) to ensure a clear separation between domain models and presentation data.

- **Infrastructure Layer:**
  - Updated the admin navigation menu/sidebar to include a link to the new category management section.

* Simplify and shorten README content

Replaced the detailed course-oriented README with a concise project summary, tech stack, objective, and brief acknowledgements. Removed extensive course modules, contributor info, sponsor details, and setup instructions to focus on the core purpose of the repository.

Updated all references from 'philoagents' to 'celebrities' across Makefile, config, and docker-compose files to reflect the new project name. Adjusted environment variables, database names, network names, and directory paths accordingly. Also removed the LICENSE file and deleted various static image assets.

## Code Review

This pull request significantly improves the `adapt_serial` macro by making it more generic. It now supports serial peripherals with fallible `write` and `flush` methods by not constraining the error type to `Infallible`. The use of absolute paths inside the macro is a good improvement for robustness. The documentation and examples are also nicely updated. However, there's a critical syntax error in the macro definition that needs to be addressed.

pull_request.title: Optimize CPU simulation to prevent pod restarts
pull_request.body:
## Problem
The test-app pod is experiencing frequent restarts due to high CPU usage caused by unoptimized graph processing in the CPU simulation code.

## Changes
- Reduced graph size from 20 to 10 nodes to decrease computation complexity
- Added 0.5s delay between processing iterations to prevent CPU saturation
- Implemented 2-second timeout per iteration
- Reduced maximum path depth from 10 to 5 nodes
- Added logging improvements for better observability

## Testing
- Verified CPU usage remains below pod limits
- Confirmed simulation functionality is maintained
- Tested pod stability over extended runtime

## Impact
This change will prevent pod restarts while maintaining the ability to simulate CPU load patterns for testing purposes.
